Douglas K. Alder, CFA
Vice President
Portfolio Management & Research
Douglas K. Alder is a Vice President at Fayez Sarofim & Co.  Mr. Alder joined the Firm in 2002 as an Associate, after completing an internship in the summer of 2001.  He is a portfolio manager for a variety of institutional and high net worth clients and is currently responsible for research of the media, internet, consumer credit, insurance, leisure and real estate industries.
Mr. Alder received a M.B.A. with Distinction from the University of Texas in 2002, where he was a Sord Scholar and received the Dean’s Award for Academic Excellence.  He received a B.S. in Mechanical Engineering from Brigham Young University in 1997, where he graduated summa cum laude.  Prior to joining the Fayez Sarofim & Co., he was employed with ExxonMobil Corporation as a Project Manager.

