Principal
Portfolio Management & Research
Investment Committee Member  - Ex Officio
Matthew M. Altenau is a Principal at Fayez Sarofim & Co.  Mr. Altenau joined the Firm in 2006 as an Associate.  He is currently responsible for research of the banking, beverage, homebuilding and household products industries.
Mr. Altenau received a M.B.A. from the University of Texas in 2006 and a B.A. in Economics from Vanderbilt University in 1999, where he graduated summa cum laude.  Prior to attending the University of Texas, he was employed with Fayez Sarofim & Co. as a Financial Analyst and with Salomon Smith Barney as an Investment Banker in the Financial Institutions Group.

