Mr. Gracely received a M.B.A. from Stanford University in 2007 and a B.B.A. in Business Administration from the University of Texas in 2002, where he graduated with High Honors.  Prior to joining Fayez Sarofim & Co., he managed the Investments, Mergers and Acquisitions group at EDP Renewables and worked in the investment banking division of Morgan Stanley.  
Mr. Gracely serves on the boards of the Blue Cure Foundation and the Footprints Family Foundation.  He is also the Co-President of the Houston Chapter of the Stanford G.S.B. Alumni Association.  

