Investment Committee Member
Charles E. Sheedy is a Senior Vice President at Fayez Sarofim & Co. and a member of the Firm’s Investment Committee.  He is co-manager of the mutual funds that Fayez Sarofim & Co. manages for The Dreyfus Corporation and serves on the board of Sarofim Trust Co.  Additionally, he is a portfolio manager for a variety of institutional and high net worth clients.  Mr. Sheedy joined the Firm 1971 as an Associate.  Over the years, areas of responsibility have included retail, electrical equipment, consumer staples, basic industries and health care.
Mr. Sheedy received a M.B.A. from Harvard Business School in 1971 and graduated cum laude from the University of Notre Dame in 1969.
Mr. Sheedy is a member of the Notre Dame Arts & Letters Advisory Counsel.

